WARRI – The leadership of the Niger Delta Youth Council Of Nigeria (NDYCN), Delta State chapter, has called on the Federal Government to stop inflicting hardship on Nigerians. The council made the call through its state Chairman, Comrade Omoniyi U. Freedom, in an interview with newsmen in Asaba. He described the proposed increase in the pump price of PMS by the Federal Government to N302, as a way to punish Nigerians, adding that if implemented, it would cause chaos, anarchy and pain in the country. Foreign Group To Renovate Olumirin Water Fall To Boost Osun… Osun Alleviating Poverty Through Social Intervention Programmes… The Delta State chairman urged the government to meet up to provide basic amenities for the people, focus on security and curb insurgency in order to protect the life and property of her citizens besides fighting inflation to stabilize the economy. He added that Nigerians had endured so much hardship and bad governance from the Buhari administration, calling on Nigerian youths to rise and speak up against the proposed plan.